insular /ˈɪnsjʊlə/

1. ADJ If you say that someone is insular , you are being critical of them because they are unwilling to meet new people or to consider new ideas. 与世隔绝的; 保守的 [表不满] 

例： They were an insular family. 他们一家人与世隔绝。 

2. insularity N-UNCOUNT 保守 

例： But at least they have started to break out of their old insularity. 但他们至少已经开始打破以前的保守状态了。

